<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>Hi, I need to transform an org table from </p> <p>| foo1 |<br/> | foo2 |<br/> | foo3 |<br/> | foo4 |<br/> | foo5 |<br/> | foo6 |<br/> | foo7 |<br/> | foo8 |<br/> | foo9 |<br/> | foo10 |</p> <p>To a text like this:</p> <p>foo1<br/> + foo3<br/> + foo4<br/> + foo5<br/> + foo6<br/> Bar: foo8</p> <p>That is: I need to get rid of the vertical bars, trailing whitespaces and of some fixed lines (lines 2, 7, 9 and 10), and then I need to prepend certain lines (3-6) with &quot;+ &quot; and another line (line 8) with &quot;Bar: &quot;.</p> <p>I tried with macros but it gets too complex, so I guess I need to write a function to do just that. I&#39;m not elisp fluent at all and I&#39;m hoping the elisp wizards can give me a hand. </p> <p>Thanks in advance!</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/inwit_"> /u/inwit_ </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/138ib9q/transform_an_org_table/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/138ib9q/transform_an_org_table/">[comments]</a></span>